{"title": "Finance should pay much more attention to undersea cables risk", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-08-02", "content": "What is the greatest tail risk stalking global finance today? There is a depressingly long list of options: surging debt, volatile rates, geopolitical conflict and/or cyber failures like the one accidentally unleashed by CrowdStrike and Microsoft.\nBut there is another deserving far more debate: underwater sea cables."}